<t>
<field>MANAGED.ACCOUNT</field>
<desc>
            <p> Level of account management for this type of report</p>
            <p />
            <p>     Must be a valid MANAGED.ACCOUNT id.</p>
            <p />
            <p>    Mandatory if CST.DEF.TEMP, CST.DEF.FREQ, CST.EXT.DAYS or CST.LOG.RET.PRD have been specified.</p>
        </desc>
</t>
<t>
<field>AM.REP.PARAM.ID</field>
<desc>
            <p>Record key for AM.RE.PARAMETER.  Must be set to SYSTEM.</p>
            <p />
            <p>  System level parameter only.</p>
            <p />
            <p>
                <p>Validation Rules:</p>
            </p>
            <p />
            <p>     Mandatory</p>
        </desc>
</t>
<t>
<field>CST.DEF.FREQ</field>
<desc>
            <p />
            <p>     Specifies the default frequency to be used for the customer type specified in field CUSTOMER.TYPE</p>
            <p />
            <p />
            <p>     Allowed values:</p>
            <p />
            <p />
            <p>     B(snss) (Every business day) Next working day after today </p>
            <p />
            <p />
            <p>     T(wmth) (Twice a month, 15th and last day) The next 15th or month end from today, whichever is sooner </p>
            <p />
            <p />
            <p>     Wn (Every n weeks) n weeks from today</p>
            <p />
            <p />
            <p>     Mnndd (Every nn months on the dd day)</p>
            <p />
            <p>
                <p>Validation Rules:</p>
            </p>
            <p />
            <p />
            <p>     Optional</p>
        </desc>
</t>
<t>
<field>CST.DEF.TEMP</field>
<desc>
            <p />
            <p>     Defines the default report template to be used for the customer type specified in field CUSTOMER.TYPE</p>
            <p />
            <p />
            <p>     The value should exist as a record in file AM.REP.TEMPLATE</p>
            <p />
            <p />
            <p />
            <p />
            <p />
            <p>     1-15 Alphanumeric       characters.</p>
            <p />
            <p>     Optional</p>
        </desc>
</t>
<t>
<field>CST.EXT.DAYS</field>
<desc>
            <p />
            <p>     Specifies the number of days after statement date, to be used for the purpose of extracting the data for the customer type specified in field CUSTOMER.TYPE.</p>
            <p />
            <p>
                <p>Validation Rules:</p>
            </p>
            <p />
            <p />
            <p>     Only Numeric data.</p>
            <p />
            <p>     Optional</p>
        </desc>
</t>
